The paper deals with the extension of higher-order pushdown automata to recognize languages of data words. This falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory, which is covered by cs.FL. The paper also discusses the relationship between the new automaton model and the original model of higher-order pushdown automata, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.THEORY). The use of infinite alphabets and data values also suggests a connection to the field of logic and computation (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the use of stacks, which is a data structure commonly used in computer science, and thus could be categorized under cs.DS. Finally, the paper discusses the recognition power of deterministic automata with collapse, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL).
